cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SY, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the depth relation among triangles in 3-space. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely, as the paper presents a subquadratic algorithm for cutting the triangles into connected semi-algebraic pieces. 
- cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is another possible category, as the problem of eliminating depth cycles is motivated by hidden-surface removal in computer graphics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) are less likely categories, but they may be relevant due to the use of algebraic and recursive techniques in the paper.
